'  VISUAL: BOARD STATE
' ====================================================================
note as VISUAL #FFFDE7
    **Visual: Board state example.**

    "After 5 moves:"
    "  X | O | X"
    " ---|---|---"
    "  O | X |  "
    " ---|---|---"
    "    |   | O"

    "Player1 (X) plays at (2,0):"
    "  X | O | X"
    " ---|---|---"
    "  O | X |  "
    " ---|---|---"
    "  X |   | O"

    "checkForWinner(2, 0, X):"
    "  Row 2: X _ O -> NO"
    "  Col 0: X O X -> NO"
    "  Main diag (2!=0): skip"
    "  Anti-diag (2+0!=2): skip"
    "  No winner yet."

    "Player1 (X) later plays at (1,2):"
    "  X | O | X"
    " ---|---|---"
    "  O | X | X"
    " ---|---|---"
    "  X |   | O"
    "  Anti-diag: X X X -> WIN!"
end note


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:**
    "Player1 (X) and Player2 (O) take turns via
    deque round-robin. Each turn: validate move,
    place piece on 3x3 Board, check row + col +
    diagonals for win. If board full with no winner
    -> DRAW."

    "**Key design decisions:**
    1. **PlayingPiece hierarchy** — X and O as subclasses.
       Extensible for new piece types.
    2. **Deque round-robin** — supports N players.
    3. **O(N) win check** — only check the row/col/diag
       touched by the last move, not entire board.
    4. **Board validates** — addPiece() returns false
       for occupied cells. Game retries.
    Simple, clean, no over-engineering."
end note


