legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern / Concept |= Key Point |
    | 1 | TicTacToeGame orchestrates: board, players, loop | Orchestrator | initializeGame() + startGame() |
    | 2 | Player has PlayingPiece (X or O via inheritance) | Inheritance | PlayingPiece -> PlayingPieceX/O |
    | 3 | Board: NxN grid of PlayingPiece*, addPiece + getFreeCells | Composition | nullptr = empty cell |
    | 4 | Deque pops front, pushes back for turn rotation | Circular Queue | Supports N players |
    | 5 | Check row + col + main diagonal + anti-diagonal | Win Detection | O(N) per move, not O(N^2) |
    | 6 | Loop: print -> get input -> validate -> place -> check win | Game Loop | DRAW if no free cells |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Core insight**: Only check the row/col/diag that the last move touches. O(N) not O(N^2). |  |  |
endlegend

